HOUSE BILL No. 1386
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 35-31.5-2-195.6; IC 35-45-21-6.
Synopsis: Massage establishment liability insurance. Makes it a Class
A misdemeanor if a person operates a massage establishment and
knowingly or intentionally employs an individual who: (1) is providing
massages; and (2) does not have certain professional liability
insurance.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Heaton, Bartlett
January 8, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Courts and Criminal Code.
2026 IN 1386—LS 6782/DI 107

