HOUSE BILL No. 1386
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
criminal law and procedure.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 35-31.5-2-195.6 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
2 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 195.6. "Massage establishment",
4 for purposes of IC 35-45-21-6, has the meaning set forth in
5 IC 35-45-21-6(a).
6 SECTION 2. IC 35-45-21-6 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
7 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
8 1, 2026]: Sec. 6. (a) As used in this section, "massage
9 establishment" means a facility where massage therapy is
10 provided. The term does not include the following:
11 (1) The office of a licensed health care practitioner (as defined
12 in IC 20-34-5-4), if the licensed health care practitioner
13 employs a massage therapist to perform massage therapy on
14 the patients of the licensed health care practitioner.
15 (2) A public lodging establishment, if the massage therapy is
16 provided for persons at the public lodging establishment.
17 (3) The residence of a massage therapist who provides
2026 IN 1386—LS 6782/DI 107

2
1 massage therapy at the massage therapist's residence, if the
2 massage therapist is the only person providing massage
3 therapy at the residence.
4 (b) A person who operates a massage establishment and
5 knowingly or intentionally employs an individual who:
6 (1) provides massages; and
7 (2) does not have professional liability insurance with
8 minimum coverage of two million dollars ($2,000,000) per
9 claim and six million dollars ($6,000,000) in aggregate;
10 commits a Class A misdemeanor.
